http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/news/Indrani%E2%80%99s-judicial-custody-extended/article13981582.ece

The judicial custody of Indrani Mukerjea, the prime accused in the Sheena Bora murder case, has been extended till January 16. A special court judge H S Mahajan extended the custody of Indrani and will be produced again in court on January 16.Indrani’s daughter Vidhie, who is completing her education in UK, was present with her mother when the court extended her judicial custody.Advocate Gunjan Mangla, appearing for Indrani moved an application asking the court to allow Indrani to sign certain documents and cheques, photocopies of which were submitted in court. Meanwhile, an application seeking permission to allow home food for accused number two and former husband of Indrani, Sanjeev Khanna, was yet again rejected. — Special Correspondent